FBIS4-21727 "jptot014__l94027" JPRS-TOT-94-014-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 26 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO Update on Colosio Assassination Update on Colosio Assassination Assassin Cites Ties to Several Groups PA2603171694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 26 Mar 94 PA2603171694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Spanish BFN [From the ``ACIR Radio News'' newscast] [Text] Mario Aburto Martinez, who assassinated Luis Donaldo Colosio Murrieta, had maintained ties with several armed groups in various Mexican states, according to his testimony before the attorney general moments after murdering the PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] candidate. Aburto refused, however, to name the armed groups and the regions in which they operate or to say whether he acted alone or if the assassination was part of a plot. He also denied belonging in the past or at present to any political party or religious sect.
